The report acknowledges some uncertainty over whether climate change would alter the amount of precipitation in the basin.
Noting that farms remain the dominant water user in the Colorado basin, the report called agricultural water "the most important and perhaps final large reservoir of available water for urban use in the arid U.S.
Last year about 30 percent of the agency "'s" water deliveries came from the Colorado, which provides about 10 percent of California "'s" overall urban and agricultural supplies.
